{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Improve regulations of holiday rental properties",
        "additional_details": "We feel that when you purchase a home, you want to live peacefully with minimal disruption. We have found that the owners, local authorities and police won\u2019t respond to nuisance guests complaints and often rely on a complaint directly to the rental companies in the hope the listing is suspended. We feel this isn\u2019t right. We believe that home owners/tenants are expected to put up with noise, rubbish, parking issues and security concerns whilst the property owner lines their pocket!",
        "background": "We want neighbours of adjoining properties to have a legal right to be consulted before a property can be turned into a holiday rental/short term let. ",
